Hi Mark,

 

I torqued the gland nut to 250 ft lbs. I have seen values from 215 to 250,
this is the first time I saw 265 ft lbs. There is not o-ring in this set up.
I'm not sure why, but I have never seen this o-ring in any engine work I
have done.

 

The gas heater is not a priority, as it is still warm here, I plan on
running the bus for another month or two, then bringing it into the garage
for a big overhaul/cleanup etc. I'll address the gas heater at that point.
Thanks for the starting info.

 

Thanks again to all who have helped me in this swap. I am now thinking about
the battery. I plan on picking one up today. Are the optima ones worth it?
Any ideas on what I should be looking for? I'm thinking to just ask for
whatever battery is designed for a '67 12V bus.

 

 

-Kevin

 

