hey kevin  sounds good so far. I have a crankshaft with a flywheel attached
to it for grinding out the bellhousings, makes it easier to turn.Do not
forget the o ring in the flywheel and torqueing the gland nut to 265 ft-lbs.
I have ran these 6V gas heaters by using the resistor that comes in late
golfs,jettas for the fan motors, test the voltage and one of the outlets is
6 V.   they get the different speeds for the 12V fans by varing the voltage.
later  mark d


 





